<p>SolTake.com (hereinafter referred to as the "Platform") places great importance on the privacy of its users and is committed to protecting personal data. This privacy policy explains how SolTake.com collects, uses, and protects the personal information of its users.</p>

<h2>1. Information Collected</h2>
<p>SolTake.com collects the following personal information from its users:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>First and Last Name:</strong> Used to identify the user. Sharing this information is optional for the user.</li>
    <li><strong>Biography:</strong> It is used to facilitate the recognition of the user by other users. Sharing this information is optional for the user.</li>
    <li><strong>Profile Image:</strong> A digital photograph that visually represents the user. Sharing this information is optional for the user.</li>
    <li><strong>Email Address:</strong> Used for communication with users, account creation, password reset, and sending notifications.</li>
    <li><strong>The Questions and Their Multimedia Contents:</strong> Users can upload questions they have not solved to the platform and share them with other users. These questions are collected for the purpose of improving the platform's functionality and user experience.</li>
    <li><strong>The Solutions and Their Multimedia Contents:</strong> Users can upload their solutions to questions (video, text, and images) to the platform. These solutions are collected as user-contributed content and made available for access by other users.</li>
</ul>
<p>The data collected is the minimum necessary for users to effectively use the platform and share content.</p>

<h2>2. Purpose of Data Usage</h2>
<p>The personal data collected may be used for the following purposes:</p>
<ul>
    <li>To provide access to the platform and manage user accounts,</li>
    <li>To enable interaction between users (sharing problems, providing solutions, etc.),</li>
    <li>To provide technical support and resolve user complaints,</li>
    <li>To improve the overall functionality of the platform and enhance user experience.</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
<p>SolTake.com may use cookies to enhance user experience and monitor platform performance. Cookies are small data files stored on your browser that help maintain user sessions. Users can disable cookies in their browser settings, but doing so may affect the proper functioning of some platform features.</p>

<h2>4. Sharing of Data</h2>
<p>SolTake.com shares personal information of its users only in the following cases:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Hosting Provider:</strong> Used to host the platform and has access only to the technical information necessary to ensure the smooth operation of the platform.</li>
</ul>
<p>SolTake.com does not share, sell, or rent users' personal information to any other third party.</p>

<h2>5. Data Security</h2>
<p>SolTake.com takes appropriate technical and administrative measures to protect user data. Security protocols are regularly updated to prevent unauthorized access, data loss, or misuse of personal information. Data is stored securely on encrypted servers.</p>

<h2>6. User Rights</h2>
<p>Users have the right to request access to, update, delete, or stop the processing of their personal data provided to SolTake.com. These requests include account termination or revoking consent for data processing. To make a request, users can contact us by emailing <a href="mailto:info@soltake.com">info@soltake.com</a>.</p>

<h2>7. Data Retention Period</h2>
<p>User data is retained as long as the account remains active on the platform. When an account is closed or usage is terminated, the data is deleted as soon as possible.</p>

<h2>8. International Data Transfers</h2>
<p>SolTake.com only transfers personal data to international hosting providers in compliance with local data protection laws. All necessary measures are taken to ensure the protection of personal data during such transfers.</p>

